      <body>
         <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
<ab><lb n="1"/>  <persName type="emperor"><name nymRef="#Δροῦσος">Δροῦσον</name>  <name nymRef="#Καῖσαρ">Καίσαρα</name>  <lb n="2"/><persName type="emperor"><name nymRef="#Τιβέριος">Τιβερίου</name></persName>  <w lemma="υἱός">υἱόν</w>  </persName></ab>
</div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>(Statue of) Drusus Caesar, son of Tiberius.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>One of the Sebasteion group of dedications to the imperial family (<ref type="inscription" n="1315" target="iAph090037"/>=72.224, <ref type="inscription" n="1316" target="iAph090038"/>=72.237, <ref type="inscription" n="1317" target="iAph090039"/>=72.275, <ref type="inscription" n="1318" target="iAph090040"/>=73.145, <ref type="inscription" n="1296" target="iAph090033"/>=77.123, <ref type="inscription" n="1288" target="iAph090026"/>=80.172, <ref type="inscription" n="1289" target="iAph090027"/>=82.108, <ref type="inscription" n="1298" target="iAph090035"/>=82.109, <ref type="inscription" n="1290" target="iAph090028"/>=82.116, <ref type="inscription" n="1297" target="iAph090034"/>=82.117, <ref type="inscription" n="1291" target="iAph090029"/>=82.118, <ref type="inscription" n="1299" target="iAph090036"/>=82.210, <ref type="inscription" n="1293" target="iAph090030"/>=84.30, <ref type="inscription" n="1294" target="iAph090031"/>=84.31, and  <ref type="inscription" n="1295" target="iAph090032"/>=84.41). On these see <bibl><ptr target="jmr1996b"/>
                  <author>Reynolds</author> (1996), <title level="a">Ruler-cult at Aphrodisias</title>
               </bibl>.</p>
            <p>For another dedication to Drusus see <bibl>
                  <title level="m"> Jahreshefte</title> 53 (1981/82), 155, no.144</bibl>. There, however, father and son receive their full titulature. Tiberius' lack of titles might suggest a date before his accession, or after his death.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="bibliography">
            <p>mentioned by <bibl><ptr target="jmr1986"/>
                  <author>Reynolds</author>, StudClas 24, 1986, 112</bibl>; by <bibl><ptr target="rrrs1987"/>
                  <author>Smith</author>, JRS 77, 1987, 95</bibl>, whence  <bibl><ptr target="mccabePHI"/>
                  
                  <citedRange><ref target="https://epigraphy.packhum.org/text/257074">195</ref></citedRange>
               </bibl>. Published, with the statue fragments, by <bibl><ptr target="rrrs2006"/>
                  <author>Smith</author>, <title>Roman Portrait Statuary from Aphrodisias</title>, no. <citedRange>27</citedRange>
               </bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="iaph2007"/> <citedRange unit="entry"><ref target="http://insaph.kcl.ac.uk/iaph2007/iAph090028.html">9.28</ref></citedRange></bibl>.</p>
         </div>
